title: Photos: At least 2,000 gathered in Austin on Tuesday for Texas Muslim Capitol Day | Dallas News |
text: Hiba Loya and Donia Kased, both of Houston, join in as the national anthem is sung outside the Texas Capitol during the Texas Muslim Capitol Day rally in Austin on Tuesday, January 31, 2017. Vernon Bryant/Staff Photographer Naheda Khan and daughter Meherina Khan, 18 of Houston clap as they cheer for America during a press conference at the steps of the Texas Capitol during the Texas Muslim Capitol Day rally in Austin on Tuesday, January 31, 2017. Vernon Bryant/Staff Photographer People gather as the national anthem is sung outside the Texas Capitol during the Texas Muslim Capitol Day rally in Austin on Tuesday, January 31, 2017. Vernon Bryant/Staff Photographer A statue on top of the Texas Capitol dome during the Texas Muslim Capitol Day rally in Austin on Tuesday, January 31, 2017. In November 1985 the original Goddess of Liberty was removed by helicopter. A new statue, cast of aluminum in molds made from the original zinc statue, was placed on the dome in June 1986.
